  "accountingRefund": {
    "noAbsences": "No no-shows in the manifest - the refund block is not needed.",
    "yes": "yes",
    "no": "no",
    "howRefundsWorkTitle": "How no-show refunds work (for the accountant)",
    "step1": "The guide records a no-show in the manifest - then the <strong>manager</strong> works on the booking card.",
    "step2": "If a refund is <strong>not due under the rules</strong>, the manager picks the no-refund option: the tourists are counted everywhere as having traveled, <strong>your review of this line is not needed</strong> - the list will show a \"refund not required\" mark.",
    "step3": "If a refund is needed (often with cost deductions, e.g. a guideline of ~70% of the payment after ~30% withheld - the manager sets the specifics in the comment), the manager enters the amount, explains the situation and attaches a photo/certificate if needed.",
    "step4": "<strong>Your job</strong> is to use the comment and attachments to make sure the refund is justified: \"Approve refund\" or \"Reject\". If rejected, the internal policy applies (a refund already paid to the client without sufficient grounds may be withheld from the responsible manager).",
